Product description

Color:White

Stylus Pencil for iPad Pro 2021, iPad Pro 4th & 3rd Generation, iPad Air 4th & 3rd Generation, iPad 8th/7th/6th Generation, iPad mini 5

Wide Compatibility
iPad Pro 2021, iPad Pro 4th & 3rd Generation, iPad Air 4th & 3rd Generation, iPad 8th/7th/6th Generation, iPad mini 5.

IPad Pro, IPad, IPad Air, IPad Mini 2018-2021
Designed for these iPad tablets launched 2018 and after.

How to use
Double tap the cap to turn on, and double tap the cap to turn off.

Pixel precision
Using advanced technology, the Stylus can accurately locate each pixel and work like an A pple pencil

Palm Rejection
Active Stylus. You can use the Stylus like a real pencil on paper, you can rest your palm on the iPad display.

Tap the Screen to make a quick note
Tap your iPad display with the Stylus to open the Notes app and collect your ideas easily.

Magnetic
Can be magnetically stored on the iPad Pro, iPad, iPad Air, iPad mini 2018-2021.

Tilt Creative
This pen contains tilt pressure sensors. The tilt angle reflects the different thickness and concentration of the line.

Fast Charging
Premium Lithium Battery. USB C fast charging. 1 minute = 30 minutes to use. charging time: less than 1 hour.

Beauty
A slim and elegant aluminum pencil body design.

What You Get
1* AZX Palm Rejection Active Pencil + 2* Additional Replacement Tips + 1* USB C Cable + 1* User manual.

Warranty
We Provide 12-Month Warranty AND Lifetime Technical Support.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality for the price
      Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2021
      Color: WhiteVerified Purchase
      Let me start off by saying I haven’t used the “apple pencil”. I bought this first before shelling out $150 for the apple version. So far I’m super impressed by the quality of this. I don’t know how the apple version could be much better than this. The only issue I have with this is how sensitive the on/off switch is. I accidentally hit it all the time but it’s not that big of a deal. It’s super convenient that it magnetizes to the top of iPad. I have the new 2021 12.9 inch pro version if that makes a difference I’m not sure. Like I said I wish the on/off switch was a button you had to press and not a ‘touch’ version. If you’re trying to save over $100 then I would highly recommend this pencil. I’m getting another for my girlfriend and sister and with buying three I’m total I’ll still have spent less than 1 Apple Pencil.
